<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Divers" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Divers,</orth> 1) differing, deviating: <cit><quote>new opinions, d. and dangerous,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.3.18" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 3, 18</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) different: <cit><quote>time travels in d. paces with d. persons,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.326" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 326</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>how chance's mocks and changes fill the cup of alteration with d. liquors,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.1.53" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 1, 53</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.184" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 184</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.3.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 3, 11</bibl>.
<lb />3) several, sundry: <cit><quote>d. philosophers hold,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.236" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 236</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.263" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 263</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 202</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.7" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.262" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 262</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 1, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.218" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 218</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.1.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 1, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 1, 20</bibl>. Followed by <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>d. of Antonio's creditors,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 118</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>